===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally {{zh-m|*㞷/𫭠}}, a {{Han compound|止|王|c1=s|c2=p|t1=foot|ls=psc|nocap=y}}; see also the top component of {{zh-m|*出}}. Later {{zh-m|*彳}} was added to form {{zh-m|*𢓸}}, a {{Han compound|彳|止|王|c1=s|c2=s|c3=p|t1=to step|t2=foot|ls=psc|nocap=y}}. Eventually, the right component was stylized into the unrelated {{zh-m|*主}}. The footprint {{zh-m|*屮}} pointing upwards on top became a point as in the character {{zh-m|*之}}.

See also {{zh-l|*迋}}.

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*waŋ||to go; to come}}. Cognate with {{cog|my|ဝင်||to come in; to enter}}, {{cog|bo|འོང||to come}}, {{m|bo|ཡོང||to come}}. Related to {{och-l|于|to go}}.

