====Usage notes====
* {{sense|to, towards (a direction)}} In Hakka, it is used after a verb and before a directional term, such as {{m|hak|上||up}}, {{m|hak|下||down}}, {{m|hak|出||out}}.
* {{sense|to, towards (a state)}} In Mandarin, the state is restricted to a small set of monosyllabic adjectives/verbs and must be followed by {{zh-m|裡}} ({{zh-ref|Lü, 1999}}). In Jin, it is much more productive, and {{zh-m|裡}} is optional ({{zh-ref|Zong and Zhang, 2013}}).

